The suspects were allegedly involved in the fraudulent endorsement of documents in exchange for cash. JOHANNESBURG - The Hawks have arrested 18 people for corruption at the Ficksburg Border Post which connects South Africa and Lesotho.The suspects, 10 of them police officers, five Home Affairs officials and three runners were allegedly involved in the fraudulent endorsement of documents in exchange for cash.It s understood the suspects, some of whom were arrested while on duty, demanded payments for their shenanigans from undercover cops and they would charge between R150 and R200 per transaction.Home Affairs spokesperson Mayihlome Tshwete said: When officials engage in corruption at highly sensitive areas like ports of entry, they not only betray the trust bestowed upon them by the public, but they also expose the country to very serious security risks. 